The paper deals with the secrecy of wiretap channels, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It specifically focuses on the two-way wiretap channel with feedback, which is a subcategory of wiretap channels and falls under the security and privacy category (cs.CR). The paper also discusses achievable secrecy rate regions and outer bounds, which are common techniques in information theory and optimization (cs.SI). The use of feedback in the wiretap channel is a topic in control theory and communication networks (cs.CC). Finally, the paper deals with the transmission of confidential messages, which is a topic in networking and security (cs.NI).
